{"questionId":"9073027","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The particle omega minus (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\Omega ^ - }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) decays at rest into a neutral pion (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\pi ^0}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) and the xi baryon (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\Xi ^ - }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) according to</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><sup><span style=\"font-size:small;background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"{\\Omega ^ - } \\to {\\pi ^0} + {\\Xi ^ - }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span></sup></p>\n<p>The pion momentum is 289.7 MeV c<sup>–1</sup>.</p>\n<p>The rest masses of the particles are:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"display:inline !important;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\Omega ^ - }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span>: 1672 MeV c<sup>–2</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"display:inline !important;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\pi ^0}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span>: 135.0 MeV c<sup>–2</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\Xi ^ - }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>: 1321 MeV c<sup>–2</sup></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the speed of the pion.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\gamma&nbsp; « = \\frac{{\\sqrt {{{289.7}^2} + {{135.0}^2}} }}{{135.0}} » = 2.367\">\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>«</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>289.7</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>135.0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>135.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>»</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.367</mn>\n</math></span></span> ✔</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v «= \\sqrt {1 - \\frac{1}{{{{2.367}^2}}}} c » = 0.903c\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>«</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>−</mo>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2.367</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>»</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.903</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span> ✔</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for bald correct answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073027","referenceCode":"19M.3.HL.TZ1.b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the speed of the pion.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Additional higher level option topics)","A.4 – Relativistic mechanics (HL only)","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}